<font color="#FF0000">BEYOND VIETNAM</font><br>
<tt>Sat Dec 14 11:39:23 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
My fellow Americans-what a dear refrain that is. It was only in Vietnam and afterward that I actually really felt like an American. Life has taught me and by now most of the &quot;Baby-boomers&quot; that things are not always what they seem to be. The Vietnam experience will probably turn out to be the rallying point. It will be a &quot;centering&quot; mechanism which at some soon future moment we will cry. At the sound we will all fall into line together and our inherent American genius will surface to save us from the wandering moral morass we have allowed ourselves to fall in to. My dear precious fellow Americans- VIETNAM! 
<p><code>-- PBey280087@aol.com  (M. Corbin Bey) </code><p>


